  "response_text": "Given the constraints of exercising at home in a small space, I've created a weekly workout plan that requires minimal equipment and can be adapted to fit a small area. This plan focuses on bodyweight exercises, which are effective for building strength, improving flexibility, and increasing cardiovascular endurance.\n\n**Monday (Upper Body):**\n\n1. Warm-up: 5-10 minutes of light cardio (jogging in place, jumping jacks, etc.)\n2. Push-ups: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n3. Tricep dips (using a chair or bench): 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n4. Arm circles (holding light weights or water bottles): 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n5. Plank: 3 sets of 30-60 seconds\n6. Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of stretching\n\n**Tuesday (Lower Body):**\n\n1. Warm-up: 5-10 minutes of light cardio\n2. Squats: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n3. Lunges: 3 sets of 10-12 reps (per leg)\n4. Calf raises: 3 sets of 12-15 reps\n5. Glute bridges: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n6. Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of stretching\n\n**Wednesday (Rest day)**\n\n**Thursday (Core):**\n\n1. Warm-up: 5-10 minutes of light cardio\n2. Russian twists (using a light weight or medicine ball): 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n3. Leg raises (hanging leg raises or lying leg raises): 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n4. Bicycle crunches: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n5. Plank: 3 sets of 30-60 seconds\n6. Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of stretching\n\n**Friday (Upper Body):**\n\n1. Warm-up: 5-10 minutes of light cardio\n2. Incline push-ups (using a chair or bench): 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n3. Bicep curls (using light weights or water bottles): 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n4. Tricep extensions (using light weights or water bottles): 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n5. Shoulder press (using light weights or water bottles): 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n6. Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of stretching\n\n**Saturday (Lower Body):**\n\n1. Warm-up: 5-10 minutes of light cardio\n2. Step-ups (using a chair or bench): 3 sets of 10-12 reps (per leg)\n3. Wall sits: 3 sets of 60-90 seconds\n4. Calf raises: 3 sets of 12-15 reps\n5. Glute bridges: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n6. Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of stretching\n\n**Sunday (Rest day or active recovery)**\n\n**Additional Tips:**\n\n* Start with lighter reps and sets, and gradually increase as you build strength and endurance.\n* Focus on proper form and technique throughout each exercise.\n* Incorporate high-intensity interval training (HIIT) by adding short bursts of intense cardio (20-30 seconds) followed by rest periods (1-2 minutes).\n* Stay hydrated and listen to your body, taking rest days as needed.\n* Consider investing in a few pieces of equipment, such as resistance bands or a jump rope, to add variety to your workouts.\n\nRemember, consistency and patience are key. Stick to the plan, and you'll see improvements in your overall fitness and well-being.",
